<font color="#FF0000">MY COUSINS</font><br>
<tt>Mon Apr 14 13:29:53 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
I can't say that I feel guilt for not serving, for it was not in my control.  I got lucky and missed the war by one year.  In the lottery, my birthday was #1, but the draft stopped just one year before.  What I feel something about (guilt??) is not understanding what Vietnam was about for my cousins who did serve.  I didn't know what to say to them when they returned.  I didn't know what had happened to them.  I have tried to talk with one of them about his experiences, but have not been too successful.  I get the feeling he really doesn't want to talk about it.  I still want to talk with them, but I don't know what to say or if my need to talk is simply to relieve guilt for not talking with them 20 years ago.
<p><code>-- todos@igc.apc.org  (Hugh Vasquez) </code><p>


